OL,3,CZoe Garbett: Who is the Green Party's
OL,4,Cfirst mayor, and her teenage deputy?
OL,6,FShe says she uses her personal
OL,7,Fexperiences in her activism, writing
OL,8,Fin an interview with Bright Green in
OL,9,F2023: "Identifying as queer, I've
OL,10,Fworked to protect safe spaces for
OL,11,FLGBTIQA+ communities and to ensure
OL,12,Fthat LGBTIQA+ people see themselves
OL,13,Freflected in local NHS campaigns."
OL,15,FWhen she was announced as the Green
OL,16,FParty candidate for the 2024 London
OL,17,Fmayoral election, which she lost to
OL,18,FSadiq Khan, she said she would abolish
OL,19,Ffare zones on the London Underground,
OL,20,FOverground and DLR, and instead
OL,21,Fimplement a flat fee for travel.
OL,26,@kD@Cxr
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/13
